      "thinking": {
        "text": "\nLet me analyze both results to provide a comprehensive answer about the customer base across CLV tiers and channel preferences.\n\nFrom the customer_intelligence results:\n- Total guest base: 50,000 guests\n- PLATINUM: 741 guests (1.5%)\n- GOLD: 5,864 guests (11.7%)\n- SILVER: 22,617 guests (45.2%)\n- BRONZE: 20,778 guests (41.6%)\n\nHigh-value (Platinum + Gold): 6,605 guests (13.2%)\nStandard (Silver + Bronze): 43,395 guests (86.8%)\n\nKey CLV insights:\n- Platinum avg lifetime value: $2,479, predicted CLV: $2,671\n- Gold avg lifetime value: $1,719, predicted CLV: $1,805\n- Silver avg lifetime value: $1,468, predicted CLV: $1,546\n- Bronze avg lifetime value: $456, predicted CLV: $504\n\nFrom the channel_financial results, I can see channel preferences by CLV tier:\n\nFor PLATINUM guests:\n- Top channel: APP (10,562 orders, $262K revenue)\n- Second: IN_STORE (7,893 orders, $197K revenue)\n- Third: UBER_EATS (5,953 orders, $151K revenue)\n- Average order value: $24.75-$25.52\n\nFor GOLD guests:\n- Top channel: APP (85,411 orders, $1.94M revenue)\n- Second: IN_STORE (61,811 orders, $1.41M revenue)\n- Third: KIOSK (46,261 orders, $1.06M revenue)\n- Average order value: $22.62-$23.27\n\nKey insights:\n1. High-value guests (Platinum + Gold) represent only 13% of the customer base but show strong digital-first behavior\n2. APP is the dominant channel for high-value customers\n3. High-value customers have higher average order values ($22-25) compared to standard customers ($20-22)\n4. High-value customers show higher margins on owned channels (96-97%) vs third-party delivery (52-62%)\n\nThis is a strategic question that should be answered with clear business implications. I'll structure it as: Key finding > Data breakdown > Strategic recommendation.\n"
