    {
      "text": "\n\n**High-value customers are mobile-first and digital-savvy:**\n- **Platinum guests**: APP dominates with 10,562 orders ($262K revenue), followed by in-store and delivery. Average order value: $24.75-$25.52\n- **Gold guests**: APP leads with 85,411 orders ($1.94M revenue), then in-store ($1.41M) and kiosk ($1.06M). Average order value: $22.62-$23.27\n\n**Critical insight**: Your Platinum and Gold customers have 3-5 percentage points higher margins on owned digital channels (96-97%) compared to when they order through third-party delivery (52-62%). They're also ordering $2-5 more per transaction than Silver/Bronze guests.\n\n## Strategic Recommendation\n\n**Protect and expand your high-value digital relationship:**\n1. **Prioritize app experience for Platinum/Gold segments** - they're already there and generating the highest margins\n2. **Migration opportunity**: Your high-value customers still place 30-35% of orders through third-party delivery. Every order shifted from UberEats (28% commission) to your app saves $7+ per $25 order\n3. **Investment focus**: With only 6,605 guests driving disproportionate value, personalized retention and app-exclusive offers for this segment will have outsized ROI\n4. **Risk mitigation**: Monitor the 43,395 Silver/Bronze guests for upgrade potential - they represent your pipeline to high-value status\n",
      "type": "text"
    }
